⁣
Trying to teach something you don’t embody will only make you more confused and disconnected from yourself as you attempt to appear one way when really you’re another,⁣ and it won’t ever genuinely help the person you’re trying to teach…⁣
⁣
Because there’s no depth of understanding; no substance. ⁣
⁣
It’s not real.⁣
⁣
Too often I see this happen…⁣
⁣
•People who are broke trying to teach money mindset⁣
•People who are constantly anxious and disconnected from themselves trying to teach alignment and confidence⁣
•People who have never been in a healthy relationship teaching divine union ⁣
⁣
If you really want to help others,⁣
help yourself.⁣
⁣
Be the living example of the thing, first. ⁣
⁣
In my experience coaching isn’t something you just wake up and decide to do one day, it’s a calling that finds you after making a radical transformation in your life⁣
⁣
Any form of leadership is a calling that you don’t ‘choose’ because it ‘looks cool’ or gives you the lifestyle you desire; it’s something that finds you, it’s a byproduct of who you become, and it will constantly ask for more of you, and will evolve with you over time.⁣
⁣

Last year I wired a large amount of money to a Mentor on Instagram and it was the best-worst decision I could have ever made.⁣
⁣
I was coming out of a dysregulated state after going through health challenges & severe burn out earlier that year, and in a lapse of my better judgment & clear thinking, I made this totally irrational investment.⁣
⁣
At that moment, I believed this ‘big bold move’ would scale my coaching business from $300k/year to 7 figures annually.⁣
⁣
Why I’m now glad this happened:⁣
1. I am much more stronger and resilient having to come back from this ‘setback’. Last year was virtually my first challenging year because of my health since I started in 2017(more to come on this as I realize my version of ‘success’ is not everyone’s story and there needs to be so much more transparency & honesty online).⁣
2. I have SUCH a higher respect for money!! ⁣
3. I’m CRYSTAL CLEAR on the bottle neck that I was having in order to *sustainably* scale my business.
4. I’m not at all disillusioned to the idea that what someone says on social media is TRUTH. Use your discernment and vet any type of claim. For example, if someone is claiming to have a ‘rapidly growing 7 figure business’, ask for proof. If someone claims they’ve ‘cracked the code on multi 6 figure months’ ask for proof. If someone is claiming their business is growing 500% year after year lol ask for proof!!⁣
5. I will never defer my power to someone or something outside of me. I will never make any type of investing decisions when I’m in anything other than an empowered, clear frame of mind moving forward. ⁣
⁣
I really think this type of post needed to be made as there’s so much manipulative, inaccurate and unhelpful messaging and marketing in the coaching space here on Instagram.⁣
⁣
The coaching space can be an echo chamber in that kind of way.⁣
⁣
And Coaches, do better. Is the price tag TRULY aligned with the value you provide? ⁣
⁣
Are the clients you’re taking on in the correct state for it to be a conducive symbiotic relationship of mutual benefit and growth?⁣
⁣
Is your sales process in full integrity?⁣
⁣
Is your marketing in full integrity?⁣
(Continued)
Creation, Family, Money, Purpose! I’ll take it! What’s yours?

I’m unsure if it’s because I recently turned 33, or if it’s just the amount of LIFE I’ve been able to live these past 7 years without rushing into checking off the boxes of societal norms or expectations people love to put on us… ⁣
⁣
but something about it has me thinking about the importance of living life in accordance to what feels right for YOU, all the way down to your Soul.⁣
⁣
When I reflect on the major decisions I’ve made in my life, 90% of them have stemmed from doing the opposite of what I was “supposed to do”⁣
⁣
I grew up in a Suburb of West Philadelphia and when I was 17 moved across the country to go to College⁣
⁣
I majored in Marketing and realized pretty quickly corporate America wasn’t for me⁣
⁣
When some of my friends started having babies, I started a business⁣
⁣
When people were buying their first time homes, I decided to move to Bali (lol)⁣
⁣
So here’s a little reminder if you’re anything like me: ⁣
⁣
Timelines are ARBITRARY⁣
There is no “right” way⁣
There is no “right” time⁣
⁣
And most importantly: this is YOUR LIFE!⁣
⁣
This is not a dress rehearsal!! ⁣
⁣
True freedom and fulfillment comes from being brave enough to create a life that’s radically aligned to who YOU are as a person and your core values.⁣❤️‍🔥
⁣
We all weren’t born wanting the same things! And that’s beautiful. We were never meant to.⁣

Own who you are,
own what you want,
and do it the way you want to do it,
when you want to do it…

The rules are fake! Do you.
⁣
